---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Epigraph from '../components/Epigraph.astro';

const origin = Astro.site?.origin ?? 'https://bonarchisimeu.me';
const jsonLd = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Person',
  name: 'Bonarchi SIMEU',
  url: origin,
  jobTitle: 'Software Engineer',
  description:
    'Software engineer in Cameroon building banking and fintech systems for the CEMAC region.',
  address: {
    '@type': 'PostalAddress',
    addressLocality: 'Yaoundé',
    addressCountry: 'CM',
  },
  alumniOf: [
    'National Advanced School of Engineering, Maroua',
    'University of Yaoundé I',
    'University of the People',
  ],
  sameAs: [
    'https://github.com/bonarchisimeu',
    'https://www.linkedin.com/in/bonarchisimeu',
  ],
};
---

<Base
  title="About"
  description="Bonarchi SIMEU — software engineer in Cameroon who goes deep into a domain and builds the systems it needs. Currently in banking and fintech, on the road from engineering to leadership."
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>
  <article class="wrap prose">
    <span class="ledger-no">00</span>
    <h1>About</h1>

    <Epigraph
      quote="The capacity to learn is a gift; the ability to learn is a skill; the willingness to learn is a choice."
      author="Brian Herbert"
      source="Dune: House Harkonnen"
    />

    <p class="lede">
      I'm a software engineer based in Cameroon. My work is to go deep into a
      domain and build the systems it runs on. Right now that domain is banking,
      where the software has to be right the first time, because it's people's
      money, not a demo.
    </p>

    <!-- TODO: make this fully your own. Keep it first-person, concrete, and
         honest. Anchor to Cameroon. Do NOT name confidential employer work. -->
    <p>
      My path started in code: shipping core banking features, integrating
      mobile money rails, and learning, sometimes the hard way, what it takes to
      run software people quietly rely on. Working from Central Africa shapes how
      I think. The constraints here are real. Connectivity, regulation under the
      BEAC, the leap-frog dynamics of mobile money. They force a discipline I've
      come to value, and they're why I find this work genuinely interesting.
    </p>

    <p>
      I hold a Master's in Software Engineering and a Bachelor's in Computer
      Science. I'm now adding a Bachelor of Business Administration at the
      University of the People, on purpose. I want the language and the models of
      business to match the systems I already know how to build. The arc I'm
      walking is engineering, then leadership, then building something of my own.
    </p>

    <p>
      This site is where the two halves meet: the work I've shipped and the
      thinking behind it. If any of it is useful to you, that's the point.
    </p>

    <hr />

    <h2>Elsewhere</h2>
    <ul class="links">
      <li><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/bonarchisimeu">LinkedIn</a>, where I post regularly</li>
      <li><a href="https://github.com/bonarchisimeu">GitHub</a>, public code</li>
      <li><a href="mailto:bonarchisimeu@gmail.com">Email</a>, reach me directly</li>
    </ul>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  .prose { padding-top: 2.5rem; max-width: 44rem; }
  .lede { font-size: 1.2rem; color: var(--ink-soft); }
  .links { font-family: var(--body); }
  .links li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
</style>
